-- AstraZeneca, British Airways, Chloride, HMV: U.K., Irish Equity Preview
-- Ben Martin
-- 2010-06-30T06:26:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/british-airways-chloride-group-hmv-group-plc-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  
 The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index  fell 157.46, or 3.1 percent,
to 4,914.22. The  FTSE All-Share Index  declined 3 percent and
Ireland’s  ISEQ Index  sank 3.8 percent.  
 AstraZeneca Plc  (AZN LN): The U.K.’s second-largest
drugmaker won a U.S. court ruling that will help prevent
generic-drug makers from selling lower-cost copies of its
cholesterol medicine Crestor until 2016. The shares dropped 0.5
percent to 2,947 pence.  
 British Airways Plc  (BAY LN):  Europe’s third-biggest
carrier and Iberia Lineas Aereas de Espana SA moved a step
closer to a $6.2 billion combination after signing the merger-
plan document required to implement the transaction under
Spanish law. British Airways fell 5.9 percent to 197 pence.  
 Chloride Group Plc  (CHLD LN): Britain’s largest maker of
backup power equipment said Emerson Electric Co.’s cash offer of
375 pence a share is a “superior proposal” regarding the
agreement entered into with ABB Ltd. and it has notified ABB on
its decision. The stock rose 11 percent to 387.1 pence.  
 HMV Group Plc  (HMV LN): The music and video retailer that
also owns Waterstone’s bookstores said full-year pretax profit
excluding one-time items rose 18 percent to 74.2 million pounds
($112 million). The shares advanced 7 percent to 57 pence.  
